<article><div>
  <h3><i class="fa fa-warning"></i> CSS does a terrible default calculation of the box model.</h3>
  <h4>By default, padding and borders are added to the width and height to compute the final dimensions of the box.</h4>

  <h5>Fortunately there's a fix that tells css to assume that border and padding are already part of the box's dimensions.</h5>
  <mark>_box_sizing</mark>
  <pre class='language-css'><code>*,*:before,*:after{
  box-sizing: border-box;
}</code></pre>
  
